# shellcheck config for the sandbox shell scripts (the core deliverable).
#
# severity=warning gates regressions, not style noise: every script passes clean
# at this level today. The handful of info-level findings are benign/intentional
# and disabled explicitly (the rc `severity` floor alone does not change the exit
# code for them across shellcheck versions, so we name them):
#   - SC1091  sourcing files shellcheck can't follow (e.g. /etc/os-release) —
#             those paths only exist inside the container.
#   - SC2016  single-quoted '$VAR' kept literal on purpose (the jq program in
#             init-firewall.sh — `$p`/`$r` are jq vars, not shell).
#   - SC2020  intentional `tr ', ' '\n\n'` byte handling in init-firewall.sh.
severity=warning
disable=SC1091,SC2016,SC2020
